{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17648629","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17648629"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T20:56:46+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T20:56:46+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18325"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"18325","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18325"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.05,0.05,0.4,0.05,0.45]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11043"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74260"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11043","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11043"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18325"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"59752"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"10224"},{"type":"tags","id":"11272"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"25622"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25626"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74260","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74260"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is decreased in osteoarthritis compared to normal ageing?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Water content","Proteoglycan degradation","Proteoglycan synthesis","Modulus of elasticity","Collagen content"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EArticular cartilage is a specialised connective tissue that covers the ends of bones in synovial joints. It provides a smooth, lubricated surface for articulation and facilitates the transmission of loads with a low frictional coefficient. Changes in the composition and structure of articular cartilage can occur with ageing and in conditions such as osteoarthritis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIn osteoarthritis, there is a decrease in \u003Cstrong\u003Eproteoglycan synthesis\u003C/strong\u003E compared to normal ageing. This reduction contributes to the deterioration of cartilage structure and function. While \u003Cstrong\u003Ewater content\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003Emodulus of elasticity\u003C/strong\u003E may also be affected, the key difference in osteoarthritis is the decreased synthesis of proteoglycans, which are essential for maintaining cartilage resilience and load-bearing properties.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EWater content\u003C/strong\u003E - Water content may increase due to cartilage swelling\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProteoglycan degradation\u003C/strong\u003E - Degradation is increased, not decreased\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EModulus of elasticity\u003C/strong\u003E - This may decrease, but it is not the primary distinguishing factor\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECollagen content\u003C/strong\u003E - Collagen degradation occurs, but synthesis is not primarily decreased\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["In osteoarthritis, proteoglycan synthesis is decreased compared to normal ageing.","Articular cartilage in osteoarthritis shows increased degradation and decreased synthesis of proteoglycans.","The modulus of elasticity and water content may change in osteoarthritis, but decreased 